```

### 7. `src/ui/hotkey_overlay.rs`
- Add to the display actions list (around line 255, after `&Action::MaximizeColumn`): `&Action::FitWorkspaceColumns,`
- Add the display string (around line 474, after the MaximizeColumn line): `Action::FitWorkspaceColumns => String::from("Fit Columns to Display"),`

## Key points:
- The action name in config.kdl will automatically be `fit-workspace-columns` (knuffel derives kebab-case from CamelCase)
- `ColumnWidth::Proportion(p)` means fraction of working area width
- After setting widths, columns need `update_tile_sizes(true)` called on each
- Check how `self.data` (Vec<ColumnData>) gets its cached `width` values updated - you may need to recalculate them
- The `cancel_resize_for_column` function takes a mutable ref to the interactive_resize Option and a column ref. Since we're modifying all columns, just set `self.interactive_resize = None;`
- Look at `animate_view_offset_to_column` for scrolling the view to keep the active column visible after the resize

After implementing, run `cargo check` to verify compilation.

Extend the `FitWorkspaceColumns` action to support an optional `grid` mode that redistributes all windows into an optimal grid layout (rows × columns) to fill the display.

## Design

When `grid=false` (default): equalize existing column widths (current behavior).
When `grid=true`: collect all tiling windows from all columns, calculate optimal grid dimensions, redistribute windows into new columns with equal proportional widths.

Grid calculation: `num_cols = ceil(sqrt(window_count))`, distribute windows across columns with `ceil(window_count / num_cols)` windows per column (last column may have fewer).

## Files to modify:

### 1. `niri-ipc/src/lib.rs`
Change the existing `FitWorkspaceColumns {}` to:
```rust
/// Set all columns on the workspace to equal width, fitting them to the display.
///
/// If `grid` is true, also redistributes windows into an optimal grid layout.
FitWorkspaceColumns {
    /// Redistribute windows into a grid (rows × columns) layout.
    #[cfg_attr(feature = "clap", arg(long, default_value_t = false))]
    grid: bool,
},
```

